<subSubSection id="C3236573043BFFFCFF7FF8F3FEF876CE" pageId="9" pageNumber="330" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8636F8043BFFFCFF7FF8F3FEF876CE" blockId="9.[151,1437,1806,2013]" pageId="9" pageNumber="330">
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA043BFFFCFF7FF8F3FEC1763A" bold="true" box="[151,266,1806,1832]" pageId="9" pageNumber="330">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Head dark brown to black, antennal flagellum yellowish-brown (
<figureCitation id="13022A7D043BFFFCFC01F8F3FBA3763A" box="[1001,1128,1806,1832]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1842,1866]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-32@10.[151,1435,181,1819]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Diglyphomorphomyia spp. nov., females; 9–10. D. metallica; 9 body in dorsal view, holotype; 10 body in lateral view, holotype; 11–12. D. parva; 11 body in lateral view, paratype; 12 body in dorsal view, paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592896" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592896/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="330">Figs 11, 12</figureCitation>
); mesoscutum, axillae, dorsellum and propodeum yellowish-brown (
<figureCitation id="13022A7D043BFFFCFD82F8CFFD77765E" box="[618,700,1842,1868]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1842,1866]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-32@10.[151,1435,181,1819]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Diglyphomorphomyia spp. nov., females; 9–10. D. metallica; 9 body in dorsal view, holotype; 10 body in lateral view, holotype; 11–12. D. parva; 11 body in lateral view, paratype; 12 body in dorsal view, paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592896" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592896/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="330">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
), mesoscutellum yellowish-brown to dark brown; legs with coxae and trochanters whitish, remaining parts of legs yellowish-brown (
<figureCitation id="13022A7D043BFFFCFC67F8ABFC297662" box="[911,994,1878,1904]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1842,1866]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-32@10.[151,1435,181,1819]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Diglyphomorphomyia spp. nov., females; 9–10. D. metallica; 9 body in dorsal view, holotype; 10 body in lateral view, holotype; 11–12. D. parva; 11 body in lateral view, paratype; 12 body in dorsal view, paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592896" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592896/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="330">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
), fore wing hyaline (
<figureCitation id="13022A7D043BFFFCFB3CF8ABFAEC7662" box="[1236,1319,1878,1904]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1842,1866]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-32@10.[151,1435,181,1819]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Diglyphomorphomyia spp. nov., females; 9–10. D. metallica; 9 body in dorsal view, holotype; 10 body in lateral view, holotype; 11–12. D. parva; 11 body in lateral view, paratype; 12 body in dorsal view, paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592896" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592896/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="330">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
); pronotal collar without a carina along anterior margin (
<figureCitation id="13022A7D043BFFFCFD7BF887FD2E7686" box="[659,741,1914,1940]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1842,1866]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-32@10.[151,1435,181,1819]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Diglyphomorphomyia spp. nov., females; 9–10. D. metallica; 9 body in dorsal view, holotype; 10 body in lateral view, holotype; 11–12. D. parva; 11 body in lateral view, paratype; 12 body in dorsal view, paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592896" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592896/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="330">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
); midlobe of mesoscutum with three pairs of setae, middle pair short and weak (
<figureCitation id="13022A7D043BFFFCFEB8F863FE6876AA" box="[336,419,1950,1976]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1842,1866]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-32@10.[151,1435,181,1819]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Diglyphomorphomyia spp. nov., females; 9–10. D. metallica; 9 body in dorsal view, holotype; 10 body in lateral view, holotype; 11–12. D. parva; 11 body in lateral view, paratype; 12 body in dorsal view, paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592896" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592896/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="330">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
); mesoscutellum with sublateral grooves slightly sinuate in lateral part, joining in posterior part (
<figureCitation id="13022A7D043BFFFCFF3AF83FFEEE76CE" box="[210,293,1986,2012]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1842,1866]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-32@10.[151,1435,181,1819]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Diglyphomorphomyia spp. nov., females; 9–10. D. metallica; 9 body in dorsal view, holotype; 10 body in lateral view, holotype; 11–12. D. parva; 11 body in lateral view, paratype; 12 body in dorsal view, paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592896" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592896/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="330">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF4666700438FFFFFF7FF8CFFB10767D" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592896" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6592896" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592896/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="331" startId="10.[151,264,1842,1866]" targetBox="[151,1435,181,1819]" targetPageId="10">
<paragraph id="8B8636F80438FFFFFF7FF8CFFB10767D" blockId="10.[151,1437,1842,1903]" pageId="10" pageNumber="331">
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0438FFFFFF7FF8CFFE827659" bold="true" box="[151,329,1842,1867]" pageId="10" pageNumber="331">FIGURES 9–12.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C394D7B0438FFFFFEB9F8CEFDAF7659" box="[337,612,1843,1867]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Diglyphomorphomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0438FFFFFEB9F8CEFDE47659" box="[337,559,1843,1867]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="331">Diglyphomorphomyia</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0438FFFFFDD0F8CEFDAF7659" bold="true" box="[568,612,1843,1867]" pageId="10" pageNumber="331">spp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0438FFFFFD84F8CEFD537659" bold="true" box="[620,664,1843,1867]" pageId="10" pageNumber="331">nov.</emphasis>
, females; 
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0438FFFFFCEDF8CEFCF57659" bold="true" box="[773,830,1843,1867]" pageId="10" pageNumber="331">9–10.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C394D7B0438FFFFFCAEF8C9FC0E7659" authorityName="Hansson" authorityYear="2022" box="[838,965,1843,1867]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Diglyphomorphomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallica">
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0438FFFFFCAEF8C9FC0E7659" box="[838,965,1843,1867]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="331">D. metallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0438FFFFFC3DF8CEFC297659" bold="true" box="[981,994,1843,1867]" pageId="10" pageNumber="331">9</emphasis>
body in dorsal view, holotype; 
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0438FFFFFAC4F8CEFA8E7659" bold="true" box="[1324,1349,1843,1867]" pageId="10" pageNumber="331">10</emphasis>
body in lateral view, holotype; 
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0438FFFFFE97F8AAFE76767D" bold="true" box="[383,445,1879,1903]" pageId="10" pageNumber="331">11–12</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D7B0438FFFFFE22F8A5FDEF767D" authorityName="Hansson" authorityYear="2022" box="[458,548,1880,1903]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Diglyphomorphomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parva">
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0438FFFFFE22F8A5FDEF767D" box="[458,548,1880,1903]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="331">D. parva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0438FFFFFDD9F8AAFD82767D" bold="true" box="[561,585,1879,1903]" pageId="10" pageNumber="331">11</emphasis>
body in lateral view, paratype; 
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0438FFFFFC61F8AAFC69767D" bold="true" box="[905,930,1879,1903]" pageId="10" pageNumber="331">12</emphasis>
body in dorsal view, paratype.
</paragraph>
